a (`vibeguard-run\",\n      \"project\": \"/Users/lifcc/Desktop/code/AI/tools/vibeguard\",\n      \"source\": \"memory\",\n      \"source_type\": \"memory\",\n      \"status\": \"active\",\n      \"title\": \"VibeGuard management UI is local-first Project Operations dashboard\",\n      \"topic_key\": \"project-operations-dashboard-design\",\n      \"type\": \"decision\",\n      \"updated_at\": \"2026-06-17 09:05\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 79299,\n      \"preview\": \"On 2026-06-17, after user requested non-GUI cleanup work via threads, created GitHub issues #156-#163 for remaining non-GUI rclean gaps. Implemented two PRs from origin/main bf62d996: PR #165 fixes #156 by making `clean --plan` honor ActionPlan `deleteMode`, rejecting conflicting CLI mode flags, and\",\n      \"project\": \"/Users/lifcc/Desktop/code/AI/tools/rclean\",\n      \"source\": \"memory\",\n      \"source_type\": \"memory\",\n      \"status\": \"active\",\n      \"title\": \"Created non-GUI cleanup issues and PR fixes #164/#165\",\n      \"topic_key\": \"non-gui-cleanup-issues-prs-156-165\",\n      \"type\": \"bugfix\",\n      \"updated_at\": \"2026-06-16 16:51\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 79296,\n      \"preview\": \"Open queue on 2026-06-15 had no PRs and issues #135/#138 only. Created clean worktree /tmp/rclean-all-issues from origin/main 5a8a87e and local branch codex/fix-open-issues-135-138, commit 1b12dfe `fix scan warnings and TOCTOU coverage`. #138 root cause: scan recoverable errors (.rcleanignore parse,\",\n      \"project\": \"/Users/lifcc/Desktop/code/AI/tools/rclean\",\n      \"source\": \"memory\",\n      \"source_type\": \"memory\",\n      \"status\": \"active\",\n      \"title\": \"Fixed open issue tranche #135/#138 on local branch\",\n      \"topic_key\": \"open-issues-135-138-local-fix\",\n      \"type\": \"bugfix\",\n      \"updated_at\": \"2026-06-14 17:26\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 79304,\n      \"preview\": \"PR #110 (`Tighten threads run logging and merge gates`) was merged on 2026-06-24T09:33:16Z with merge commit `05fee6aaf030396cc78d7fbd1f937785c6f0ec73`, closing issue #107 at 2026-06-24T09:33:17Z. The final head before merge was `f75a324e2bb03c823f53ca8c0b0722155abb462e`. Three Codex review threads \",\n      \"project\": \"/Users/lifcc/Desktop/code/AI/tools/claude-arsenal\",\n      \"source\": \"memory\",\n      \"source_type\": \"memory\",\n      \"status\": \"active\",\n      \"title\": \"PR #110 merged after resolving connector merge-gate review threads\",\n      \"topic_key\": \"threads-pr110-delayed-review-recheck\",\n      \"type\": \"bugfix\",\n      \"updated_at\": \"2026-06-24 09:33\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 79303,\n      \"preview\": \"Merged bugfix for figure/grid translation layout breakage. Symptom: On docs.litellm.ai/blog/litellm-rust-launch, translated text in the Stage 1 diagram rendered vertically/heavily wrapped because whole-page/custom selectors accepted non-caption text inside a CSS-grid <figure>; inserted translation w\",\n      \"project\": \"/Users/lifcc/Desktop/code/AI/tools/page-lingo\",\n      \"source\": \"memory\",\n      \"source_type\": \"memory\",\n      \"status\": \"active\",\n      \"title\": \"Skip non-caption figure internals to avoid grid diagram translation layout breakage\",\n      \"topic_key\": \"figure-visual-grid-translation-skip\",\n      \"type\": \"bugfix\",\n      \"updated_at\": \"2026-06-23 11:01\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 79305,\n      \"preview\": \"On 2026-06-24, completed the Spellbook open GitHub issue/PR queue using the threads workflow. Merged PR #110 (`Tighten threads run logging and merge gates`) with merge commit `05fee6aaf030396cc78d7fbd1f937785c6f0ec73`, closing issue #107. Merged PR #109 (`[codex] add scoped agent contracts`) with me\",\n      \"project\": \"/Users/lifcc/Desktop/code/AI/tools/claude-arsenal\",\n      \"source\": \"memory\",\n      \"source_type\": \"memory\",\n      \"status\": \"active\",\n      \"title\": \"Closed remaining