 in the right le\",\n      \"project\": \"/Users/lifcc/Desktop/code/work/mutil-om\",\n      \"source\": \"memory\",\n      \"source_type\": \"memory\",\n      \"staleness\": {\n        \"age\": \"fresh\",\n        \"label\": \"status=active; staleness=fresh; source_anchor=untracked\",\n        \"source_anchor\": \"untracked\",\n        \"status\": \"active\"\n      },\n      \"status\": \"active\",\n      \"title\": \"Amenities map legend POI names truncate on whole words\",\n      \"topic_key\": \"amenities-map-legend-poi-truncation\",\n      \"type\": \"bugfix\",\n      \"updated_at\": \"2026-06-16 13:24\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 79301,\n      \"preview\": \"On 2026-06-18, the remem GitHub queue was handled with threads/no-merge policy. Root worktree was dirty/stale, so isolated worktrees were used. Final remote state: PR #527 head 2317fbc, #529 head ca20e46, #531 head 2b2939a; all three open PRs had CI SUCCESS, mergeStateStatus CLEAN, and no unresolved\",\n      \"project\": \"remem\",\n      \"source\": \"memory\",\n      \"source_type\": \"memory\",\n      \"staleness\": {\n        \"age\": \"fresh\",\n        \"label\": \"status=active; staleness=fresh; source_anchor=untracked\",\n        \"source_anchor\": \"untracked\",\n        \"status\": \"active\"\n      },\n      \"status\": \"active\",\n      \"title\": \"June 18 GitHub queue cleanup for PRs 527, 529, 531\",\n      \"topic_key\": \"github-queue-2026-06-18-pr527-pr531\",\n      \"type\": \"bugfix\",\n      \"updated_at\": \"2026-06-18 14:18\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 79300,\n      \"preview\": \"Chose the VibeGuard user-visible management page direction as a local-first `Project Operations` dashboard generated by the repo-local Codex App plugin, not a hosted telemetry/admin surface and not an unsupported custom Codex panel. The dashboard uses existing structured runtime data (`vibeguard-run\",\n      \"project\": \"/Users/lifcc/Desktop/code/AI/tools/vibeguard\",\n      \"source\": \"memory\",